---
import PNotes from "../components/PNotes.astro";
---

<p-slide class="center">
  <h1><span class="main-gradient">Testing your server</span> 🔍</h1>
</p-slide>

<p-slide>
  <h2 class="main-gradient">MCP Inspector</h2>
  <ul>
    <li p-fragment p-effect="from left">
      🛠️ The <span class="main-sub-gradient">official tool</span> by Anthropic — built
      alongside the protocol
    </li>
    <li p-fragment p-effect="from right">
      📮 A <span class="main-sub-gradient">"Postman for MCP"</span> — call tools,
      read resources, get prompts
    </li>
    <li p-fragment p-effect="from left">
      🔌 Works with <span class="main-sub-gradient"
        >stdio, SSE and streamable HTTP</span
      >
    </li>
    <li p-fragment p-effect="zoom">
      📡 Real-time logs and <span class="main-sub-gradient"
        >protocol validation</span
      >
    </li>
  </ul>
  <PNotes>
    <p>
      The MCP Inspector is the official tool from Anthropic, built alongside the
      protocol itself. It acts like Postman for MCP: you connect to your server,
      see the tools it exposes, and call them to inspect the raw JSON responses.
      It supports every transport we covered.
    </p>
  </PNotes>
</p-slide>

<p-slide>
  <h5 style="margin-block-end: 1em" class="center">
    <span class="main-gradient">MCP Inspector</span> — zero install 🚀
  </h5>
  <pre
    class="small-line"
    data-label-file="terminal">
<code is:raw class="language-javascript">
  # stdio server
  npx @modelcontextprotocol/inspector node server.js

  # remote / HTTP server
  npx @modelcontextprotocol/inspector
  # then paste your URL: http://localhost:3000/mcp
</code>
  </pre>
  <PNotes>
    <p>
      No installation needed — it runs directly through npx. For a stdio server
      you pass the command to launch it. For an HTTP server you just run the
      inspector and paste the server URL in the web UI. Then you get an
      interactive interface to list and call tools.
    </p>
  </PNotes>
</p-slide>
<style lang="scss">
  ul {
    li {
      margin-bottom: 1em;
    }
  }
</style>
